Peter is likely the apprentice of Jesus that we know most about from the pages of scripture.

48:32.728 --> 48:34.290
So to revisit our three mountains.

48:35.752 --> 48:40.339
On Tabor, Peter is the only voice we hear other than God's, and he suggests camping out.

48:41.280 --> 48:46.287
Stay in there forever in this cloudy, glowing place of prayer away from the chaos below.

48:46.688 --> 48:53.778
Peter, not unlike me on the streets of New York and the schoolyards of Portland, thinks he wants a prayer of escape, not one of incarnation.

48:54.978 --> 49:02.409
And on the Mount of Olives, Jesus asked Peter to keep watch with him, to stay up and pray beside him in his hour of need, and Peter falls asleep on the job.

