After three denials in the courtyard, he doesn't even show up in the crowd that sees Jesus' last breath, that here's his final prayer.

49:31.751 --> 49:34.815
Peter is absent in the very place where God is most present.

49:36.217 --> 49:46.349
And after all of that, Jesus goes to find him, not to reprimand him or condemn him or correct him, but to forgive him and restore him.

49:48.071 --> 49:50.834
So listen, I hope that you will devote yourself to prayer.

49:51.586 --> 50:05.566
I hope you will root your life in the only source of devotion that makes you more not less, but I know that no matter how strong your desire or fervent you will follow through, God is more devoted to communion with you than you will ever be to Him.

50:06.648 --> 50:14.860
God longs to hear your prayers more than you will ever long to pray them and to speak love to your soul more than you will ever long to hear His voice and receive it.

50:16.122 --> 50:19.186
So why don't we stand and we'll respond together now.

50:20.226 --> 50:22.189
Would you come Holy Spirit?

50:26.757 --> 50:30.604
Thanks for joining the Bridgestown family as we engage in this teaching series.

50:31.325 --> 50:37.275
To learn more about the life of our church and how you can get involved, visit bridgestown.church.com.

50:38.036 --> 50:46.290
If you're interested in contributing financially to Bridgestown Church and to our ministry, you can do that at bridgestown.church.gov.

50:46.818 --> 50:56.210
Wherever you're joining us from, we hope this resource blesses you and encourages you to be with Jesus, become like Jesus, and do what Jesus did.

